{
  "manifest": {
    "schemaVersion": 1,
    "name": "habit-tracker",
    "title": "Habit Tracker",
    "entrypoint": "index.html",
    "bindings": [],
    "capabilities": [
      "state:persist"
    ],
    "preferredSize": {
      "w": 4,
      "h": 3
    }
  },
  "files": {
    "README.md": "# Habit Tracker\n\nA rolling 7-day check-in grid: tap a day to mark the habit done, watch the\ncurrent streak update, and rename the habit inline — all persisted across\nreloads via the `state:persist` capability.\n\n## What it demonstrates\n\n- **`state:persist`** — the `dashboard:getState` / `dashboard:setState` bridge\n  messages (same envelope as `twenty48` and `pomodoro`). Completions are keyed by\n  local calendar date, so the 7-day window rolls forward on its own and a\n  checked day stays checked across reloads.\n- **Derived UI** — the streak count is computed from the stored completions\n  (consecutive days ending today, or yesterday if today is still blank), not\n  stored separately, so it can never drift out of sync.\n- **Theme tokens** — reads `--bg` / `--card` / `--text` / `--accent` / `--border`\n  from the host's `dashboard:theme` reply and follows the background luminance,\n  so it reads cleanly in both light and dark.\n- **No bindings, no network** — one self-contained sandboxed HTML file.\n\n## Controls\n\n- **Tap a day** — toggle that day's check. Today is highlighted; earlier days in\n  the window are tappable too, for backfilling a missed check-in.\n- **Click the title** — rename the habit (persisted, up to 40 characters).\n\n## Capability\n\n`state:persist` is declared in `widget.json`. Without the grant the parent\nreplies `capability_denied` and the tracker runs in-memory (checks reset on\nremount) — it degrades, it never breaks. To keep the persisted blob small, only\nthe last ~90 days of completions are retained.\n",
    "index.html": "<!doctype html>\n<!--\n  habit-tracker — a rolling 7-day check-in grid, and another starter that\n  exercises the `state:persist` capability (like twenty48 and pomodoro). On boot\n  it asks the parent for its saved blob (dashboard:getState) and restores which\n  days were completed plus the habit's name; each tap toggles a day and writes a\n  tiny blob back (dashboard:setState). The grid is keyed by local calendar date,\n  so the window rolls forward on its own and a completed day stays completed\n  across reloads. Both messages are gated by the \"state:persist\" capability in\n  widget.json — without it the parent replies capability_denied and the tracker\n  runs in-memory (checks reset on remount). No bindings, no network of any kind:\n  everything below is self-contained.\n-->\n<html lang=\"en\">\n  <head>\n    <meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n    <title>Habit Tracker</title>\n    <style>\n      :root {\n        color-scheme: light dark;\n        /* Theme tokens: default to system Canvas/CanvasText, overridden by the\n           parent's dashboard:theme reply (--bg/--card/--text/--accent/--border). */\n        --bg: Canvas;\n        --card: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 8%, Canvas);\n        --text: CanvasText;\n        --accent: #4f8cff;\n        --border: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 22%, transparent);\n        --muted: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 55%, transparent);\n        --cell: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 12%, transparent);\n      }\n      * {\n        box-sizing: border-box;\n      }\n      html,\n      body {\n        height: 100%;\n        margin: 0;\n      }\n      body {\n        padding: 12px;\n        font-family: var(--font-sans, system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif);\n        background: var(--bg);\n        color: var(--text);\n        display: flex;\n        flex-direction: column;\n        gap: 10px;\n        user-select: none;\n        -webkit-user-select: none;\n      }\n      header {\n        display: flex;\n        align-items: baseline;\n        gap: 8px;\n        flex: 0 0 auto;\n      }\n      h1 {\n        margin: 0;\n        font-size: 1.05rem;\n        letter-spacing: 0.3px;\n        flex: 1;\n        min-width: 0;\n        overflow: hidden;\n        text-overflow: ellipsis;\n        white-space: nowrap;\n      }\n      h1:focus {\n        outline: 2px solid var(--accent);\n        outline-offset: 2px;\n        border-radius: 3px;\n      }\n      .streak {\n        display: flex;\n        align-items: baseline;\n        gap: 4px;\n        flex: 0 0 auto;\n        font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n      }\n      .streak b {\n        font-size: 1.25rem;\n        font-weight: 800;\n        color: var(--accent);\n      }\n      .streak span {\n        font-size: 0.62rem;\n        text-transform: uppercase;\n        letter-spacing: 0.6px;\n        opacity: 0.7;\n        font-weight: 600;\n      }\n      #grid {\n        flex: 1 1 auto;\n        min-height: 0;\n        display: grid;\n        grid-template-columns: repeat(7, 1fr);\n        gap: 6px;\n      }\n      .day {\n        display: flex;\n        flex-direction: column;\n        align-items: center;\n        justify-content: center;\n        gap: 5px;\n        padding: 6px 2px;\n        border-radius: 8px;\n        background: var(--cell);\n        border: 1px solid transparent;\n        color: inherit;\n        font: inherit;\n        cursor: pointer;\n        min-height: 0;\n      }\n      .day:hover {\n        border-color: var(--border);\n      }\n      .day .dow {\n        font-size: 0.6rem;\n        text-transform: uppercase;\n        letter-spacing: 0.4px;\n        opacity: 0.7;\n        font-weight: 700;\n      }\n      .day .dom {\n        font-size: 0.7rem;\n        opacity: 0.55;\n        font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n      }\n      /* The check dot fills in when a day is completed. */\n      .day .dot {\n        width: 40%;\n        max-width: 26px;\n        aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;\n        border-radius: 50%;\n        border: 2px solid var(--muted);\n        display: flex;\n        align-items: center;\n        justify-content: center;\n        font-size: 0.8rem;\n        color: #fff8f0;\n        transition:\n          background 0.15s ease,\n          border-color 0.15s ease,\n          transform 0.12s ease;\n      }\n      .day.done .dot {\n        background: var(--accent);\n        border-color: var(--accent);\n      }\n      .day.today {\n        border-color: var(--accent);\n        background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 12%, var(--cell));\n      }\n      .day:active .dot {\n        transform: scale(0.85);\n      }\n      footer {\n        flex: 0 0 auto;\n        font-size: 0.62rem;\n        opacity: 0.6;\n        text-align: center;\n      }\n    </style>\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    <header>\n      <h1 id=\"title\" title=\"Click to rename\">Daily habit</h1>\n      <div class=\"streak\"><b id=\"streak\">0</b><span>day streak</span></div>\n    </header>\n\n    <div id=\"grid\" role=\"group\" aria-label=\"Last 7 days\"></div>\n\n    <footer>sandboxed · no network · state:persist</footer>\n\n    <script>\n      \"use strict\";\n\n      // ---- postMessage bridge helpers (v1 envelope, see packages/host/src/bridge.ts) ----\n      var reqSeq = 0;\n      function nextReqId() {\n        return \"hab-\" + Date.now().toString(36) + \"-\" + reqSeq++;\n      }\n      function post(type, extra) {\n        window.parent.postMessage(Object.assign({ v: 1, type: type }, extra || {}), \"*\");\n      }\n\n      // ---- state ----\n      var DAYS = 7;\n      var DOW = [\"Sun\", \"Mon\", \"Tue\", \"Wed\", \"Thu\", \"Fri\", \"Sat\"];\n      var name = \"Daily habit\";\n      var done = {}; // { \"YYYY-MM-DD\": true } — completed days\n\n      // Local-calendar date key (not UTC): the window should follow the viewer's day.\n      function keyOf(d) {\n        return (\n          d.getFullYear() +\n          \"-\" +\n          (\"0\" + (d.getMonth() + 1)).slice(-2) +\n          \"-\" +\n          (\"0\" + d.getDate()).slice(-2)\n        );\n      }\n      function dayOffset(n) {\n        var d = new Date();\n        d.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);\n        d.setDate(d.getDate() + n);\n        return d;\n      }\n\n      // The 7 visible dates, oldest first, ending today.\n      function windowDates() {\n        var out = [];\n        for (var i = DAYS - 1; i >= 0; i--) out.push(dayOffset(-i));\n        return out;\n      }\n\n      // Current streak: consecutive completed days ending at today, or at\n      // yesterday if today isn't checked yet (so an untouched today doesn't\n      // zero out a run in progress).\n      function computeStreak() {\n        var start = 0;\n        if (!done[keyOf(dayOffset(0))]) start = -1; // today blank → count up to yesterday\n        var count = 0;\n        for (var i = start; i > start - 400; i--) {\n          if (done[keyOf(dayOffset(i))]) count++;\n          else break;\n        }\n        return count;\n      }\n\n      // ---- rendering ----\n      var gridEl = document.getElementById(\"grid\");\n      var titleEl = document.getElementById(\"title\");\n      var streakEl = document.getElementById(\"streak\");\n      var todayKey = \"\";\n\n      function render() {\n        todayKey = keyOf(dayOffset(0));\n        gridEl.textContent = \"\";\n        var dates = windowDates();\n        for (var i = 0; i < dates.length; i++) {\n          gridEl.appendChild(dayCell(dates[i]));\n        }\n        titleEl.textContent = name;\n        streakEl.textContent = computeStreak();\n      }\n\n      function dayCell(date) {\n        var key = keyOf(date);\n        var btn = document.createElement(\"button\");\n        btn.type = \"button\";\n        btn.className = \"day\" + (done[key] ? \" done\" : \"\") + (key === todayKey ? \" today\" : \"\");\n        btn.setAttribute(\"aria-pressed\", done[key] ? \"true\" : \"false\");\n        btn.setAttribute(\"aria-label\", DOW[date.getDay()] + \" \" + date.getDate());\n\n        var dow = document.createElement(\"div\");\n        dow.className = \"dow\";\n        dow.textContent = DOW[date.getDay()];\n\n        var dot = document.createElement(\"div\");\n        dot.className = \"dot\";\n        dot.textContent = done[key] ? \"✓\" : \"\";\n\n        var dom = document.createElement(\"div\");\n        dom.className = \"dom\";\n        dom.textContent = date.getDate();\n\n        btn.appendChild(dow);\n        btn.appendChild(dot);\n        btn.appendChild(dom);\n        btn.onclick = function () {\n          toggle(key);\n        };\n        return btn;\n      }\n\n      function toggle(key) {\n        if (done[key]) delete done[key];\n        else done[key] = true;\n        render();\n        saveState(true);\n      }\n\n      // ---- rename (persisted habit name) ----\n      titleEl.addEventListener(\"click\", function () {\n        titleEl.contentEditable = \"true\";\n        titleEl.focus();\n        var range = document.createRange();\n        range.selectNodeContents(titleEl);\n        var sel = window.getSelection();\n        sel.removeAllRanges();\n        sel.addRange(range);\n      });\n      titleEl.addEventListener(\"keydown\", function (e) {\n        if (e.key === \"Enter\") {\n          e.preventDefault();\n          titleEl.blur();\n        }\n      });\n      titleEl.addEventListener(\"blur\", function () {\n        titleEl.contentEditable = \"false\";\n        var next = titleEl.textContent.replace(/\\s+/g, \" \").trim().slice(0, 40) || \"Daily habit\";\n        var changed = next !== name;\n        name = next;\n        titleEl.textContent = name;\n        if (changed) saveState(true);\n      });\n\n      // ---- state:persist (dashboard:getState / dashboard:setState) ----\n      var saveTimer = null;\n      var haveState = false; // did the parent ever answer? (else run in-memory)\n\n      // Keep the blob small: only persist completions from the last ~90 days.\n      function prune() {\n        var cutoff = keyOf(dayOffset(-90));\n        for (var k in done) {\n          if (Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(done, k) && k < cutoff) delete done[k];\n        }\n      }\n      function serialize() {\n        prune();\n        return { name: name, done: done };\n      }\n      function saveState(immediate) {\n        if (saveTimer) {\n          clearTimeout(saveTimer);\n          saveTimer = null;\n        }\n        var doSave = function () {\n          saveTimer = null;\n          post(\"dashboard:setState\", { requestId: nextReqId(), state: serialize() });\n        };\n        if (immediate) doSave();\n        else saveTimer = setTimeout(doSave, 400);\n      }\n\n      function restore(state) {\n        haveState = true;\n        if (!state || typeof state !== \"object\") return false;\n        if (typeof state.name === \"string\" && state.name.trim()) {\n          name = state.name.trim().slice(0, 40);\n        }\n        if (state.done && typeof state.done === \"object\") {\n          var next = {};\n          for (var k in state.done) {\n            if (\n              Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(state.done, k) &&\n              /^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}$/.test(k) &&\n              state.done[k]\n            ) {\n              next[k] = true;\n            }\n          }\n          done = next;\n        }\n        return true;\n      }\n\n      // ---- theme ----\n      function hexLuminance(value) {\n        if (typeof value !== \"string\" || value.charAt(0) !== \"#\") return null;\n        var hex = value.slice(1);\n        if (hex.length === 3) hex = hex[0] + hex[0] + hex[1] + hex[1] + hex[2] + hex[2];\n        if (!/^[0-9a-fA-F]{6}$/.test(hex)) return null;\n        var r = parseInt(hex.slice(0, 2), 16);\n        var g = parseInt(hex.slice(2, 4), 16);\n        var b = parseInt(hex.slice(4, 6), 16);\n        return (0.2126 * r + 0.7152 * g + 0.0722 * b) / 255;\n      }\n      function applyTheme(tokens) {\n        if (!tokens) return;\n        var root = document.documentElement.style;\n        [\"--bg\", \"--card\", \"--text\", \"--accent\", \"--border\", \"--muted\"].forEach(function (k) {\n          if (tokens[k]) root.setProperty(k, tokens[k]);\n        });\n        var lum = hexLuminance(tokens[\"--bg\"]);\n        if (lum !== null) root.colorScheme = lum < 0.5 ? \"dark\" : \"light\";\n      }\n\n      // ---- inbound messages (ignore anything without the v:1 envelope) ----\n      var stateReqId = nextReqId();\n      window.addEventListener(\"message\", function (event) {\n        var msg = event.data;\n        if (!msg || msg.v !== 1) return;\n        if (msg.type === \"dashboard:theme\") {\n          applyTheme(msg.tokens);\n        } else if (msg.type === \"dashboard:state\") {\n          if (!haveState && msg.requestId === stateReqId) {\n            restore(msg.state);\n            render();\n          }\n        } else if (msg.type === \"dashboard:error\") {\n          if (!haveState) haveState = true;\n        }\n      });\n\n      // ---- boot ----\n      render();\n      post(\"dashboard:ready\");\n      post(\"dashboard:getTheme\", { requestId: nextReqId() });\n      post(\"dashboard:getState\", { requestId: stateReqId });\n      setTimeout(function () {\n        if (!haveState) haveState = true; // standalone: no host, keep in-memory\n      }, 400);\n    </script>\n  </body>\n</html>\n"
  }
}
